## Hard Constraints (Do NOT)

<List the things specific to THIS project that agents must never touch. Examples:>

1. Do not touch production config (`.env.production`, prod-only profile files, prod manifests)
2. Do not modify third-party / external API adapter code without explicit user approval — upstream behavior needs human verification
3. Do not modify money / billing / commission logic without going through the full `codex-handoff` flow
4. Do not force-push to `main` or any protected branch
5. Do not delete migration files, even seemingly obsolete ones
6. Do not install new dependencies without explicit user confirmation

## Decision Boundaries

These need the project owner's personal sign-off, not agent autonomy:

- Commercial terms (vendor contracts, pricing, commission rules)
- Visual design beyond reusing existing patterns
- User-facing copy in new languages
- Anything touching real production data

## Collaboration Workflow

This project uses the **`codex-handoff` skill** — Claude plans, Codex implements and reviews.

When starting any non-trivial coding task, load the `codex-handoff` skill and follow its three-phase flow (PLAN → IMPLEMENT → REVIEW).

Spec artifacts live in `.agent/specs/`, review reports in `.agent/reviews/`. Both directories are committed to git as design history.

For project-wide code conduct (assumptions, simplicity, surgical changes), the `karpathy-guidelines` skill also applies.
